    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">禿頭</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>LACKING HAIR ON one's HEAD.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>[ARTIFICIAL/NATURAL]</p>
<p>[COMMON/RARE]</p>
<p>1. Tū 禿 refers to baldness as a natural condition and particularly as a defect.</p>
<p>[NATURAL]</p>
<p>2. Kūn 髡 probably refers to baldness as brought about deliberately through shaving, and the basic meaning of the word is "to shave", but the word is common in personal names where it is more likely to refer to natural baldness.</p>
<p>[ARTIFICIAL]; [[RARE]]</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>光禿禿</p>
<p>禿</p>
<p>童</p>
<p>拔頂 is inchoative, "to become bald".</p>
<p>禿頂 is inchoative, "to become bald".</p>
<p>禿子 refers to a bald person.</p>
<p>濯濯 refers figuratively to the "baldness" of mountains.</p>
<p>禿頂</p>
<p>禿鶖</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p>
        </div>
